Common dangling pointer patterns:

1. Use after free:
   free(p);
   *p = 10;  /* DANGLING: p still holds the old address */

2. Returning local address:
   int *bad() {
     int x = 42;
     return &x;  /* DANGLING: x destroyed on return */
   }

3. Stale reference:
   int *p;
   { int x = 10; p = &x; }
   *p = 20;  /* DANGLING: x out of scope */

Prevention:
   free(p); p = NULL;  /* NULL dereference is easier to debug */

